# Matrix Tree Stage-Based Redesign

Redesign the matrix tree page from a single org-chart view into a **tabbed stage-based view** matching the new screenshot. Users progress through Entry → Stage 1–13, and each tab shows who has reached that stage.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Backend API contract**: The current `GET /referrals/me/matrix` returns a tree with levels/users. For the new stage tabs, we'll need an endpoint like `GET /referrals/me/matrix-stage?stage=N` that returns the users who have qualified for a given stage. **I'll build the frontend to call this new endpoint, with a fallback to the existing data if it's not ready yet.** Please confirm this is the direction the backend will take, or let me know the exact endpoint/shape.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Stage count**: The screenshot shows Entry + Stage 1–3 visible. You mentioned 13 stages. I'll build **Entry + Stage 1–13** (14 tabs total) with horizontal scrolling on mobile. Confirm this is correct.

## Open Questions

1. **Stage API shape**: Will the backend return something like `{ stage: 3, members: [{ username, legs, status, ... }], totalMembers: 0 }`? Or will it reuse the existing `MatrixTreeResponse` format filtered by stage?
2. **"Legs" display**: The screenshot shows "0 legs" under a user. Is this the same as `directReferrals` / `activeLegs`? Or a new field?
3. **Entry tab**: Should the Entry tab keep the current full org-chart tree (PrimeNG OrganizationChart with drill-down), or should it also switch to the simpler card-based display?

## Proposed Changes

### Overview

The matrix tree page gets a complete UI overhaul:
- **Tab bar** at the top: `Entry | Stage 1 | Stage 2 | … | Stage 13`
- **Entry tab**: Keeps the existing org-chart tree (your referrals, navigation, zoom, etc.)
- **Stage tabs**: New card-based view showing isolated user nodes for users who have qualified for that stage, matching the screenshot design (trophy icon, user cards with legs + status, total member count)

---

### Component: Matrix Tree Page

#### [MODIFY] [matrix-tree.component.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/MLM-User.FE/mlm-user.fe/src/app/pages/network/matrix/matrix-tree.component.ts)

- Add `activeTab` signal: `'entry' | number` (number = stage 1–13)
- Add `stageTabs` array: `[{ label: 'Entry', value: 'entry' }, { label: 'Stage 1', value: 1 }, ..., { label: 'Stage 13', value: 13 }]`
- Add `stageMembers` signal to hold users returned for the active stage
- Add `stageTotalMembers` signal for total count
- Add `stageLoading` signal
- Add `onTabChange(tab)` method — when `'entry'`, use existing tree logic; when a stage number, call new service method
- Add `loadStageData(stage: number)` method — calls `networkService.fetchMatrixStage(stage)`
- Keep all existing org-chart logic intact (it only renders when `activeTab === 'entry'`)

#### [MODIFY] [matrix-tree.component.html](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/MLM-User.FE/mlm-user.fe/src/app/pages/network/matrix/matrix-tree.component.html)

Major template rewrite:

1. **Tab bar** — horizontal scrollable strip at the top with Entry + Stage 1–13 buttons. Active tab has a distinct bottom border and bold text (matching the screenshot's blue text + underline).

2. **Entry tab content** — wraps the existing org-chart tree (unchanged logic, just wrapped in `@if (activeTab() === 'entry')`)

3. **Stage tab content** — new `@if (activeTab() !== 'entry')` block:
   - Stage header card with trophy emoji + "Stage N" title
   - User node cards displayed in a centered layout:
     - Vertical connector line from top
     - Card with user icon, username, legs count, ACTIVE/INACTIVE badge
     - Green border for active, gray for inactive
   - Footer showing "Total: N members"
   - Empty state when no members have reached the stage

---

### Service: Network Service

#### [MODIFY] [network.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/MLM-User.FE/mlm-user.fe/src/app/services/network.service.ts)

- Add `StageMember` interface: `{ id, username, legs, status, stage, rank }`
- Add `fetchMatrixStage(stage: number)` method:
  - Calls `referralService.getMatrixStage(stage)` 
  - Falls back to filtering existing downline data by stage if endpoint is unavailable
  - Returns `Observable<{ members: StageMember[], totalMembers: number }>`

#### [MODIFY] [referral.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/HP/OneDrive/Documents/MLM-User.FE/mlm-user.fe/src/app/services/referral.service.ts)

- Add `MatrixStageResponse` interface
- Add `getMatrixStage(stage: number)` method:
  - `GET /referrals/me/matrix-stage?stage={stage}`
  - Fallback to `GET /referrals/me/matrix-level?level={stage}` if 404
  - Maps response to normalized `MatrixStageResponse`

---

### No Route Changes Needed

The tabs are internal to the `matrix-tree` component — no new routes required. The existing `/network/matrix` route stays as-is.

---

### Visual Design (matching screenshot)

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Entry    Stage 1    Stage 2   [Stage 3]  ...        │  ← tab bar
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                      │
│  🏆 Stage 3                                          │  ← stage header
│                                                      │
│              │                                       │  ← connector line
│         ┌─────────┐                                  │
│         │  👤      │                                  │  ← user card
│         │ osigla   │                                  │
│         │ 0 legs   │                                  │
│         │ ACTIVE   │                                  │
│         └─────────┘                                  │
│                                                      │
│  Total: 0 members                                    │  ← footer
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

When multiple users reach the same stage, their cards display in a row/grid with connector lines from a shared root line.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run build` — ensure no compilation errors
- `npm run test` — run existing tests to verify no regressions

### Manual Verification  
- Navigate to `/network/matrix` in the browser
- Verify the Entry tab shows the existing org-chart tree
- Click Stage 1–13 tabs and verify loading/empty states render correctly
- Verify the tab bar scrolls horizontally on mobile viewports
- Confirm the stage view matches the screenshot design (trophy, user cards, connector lines)
